IMPORTANT - which FFmpeg build to bundle
----------------------------------------
Only bundle an LGPL build of ffmpeg.exe. Do NOT bundle a build compiled with
--enable-gpl (for example builds that include x264/x265) or with
--enable-nonfree, because:

  * A GPL build would require this entire application to be released under the
    GPL.
  * A "nonfree" build cannot be legally redistributed at all.

This app only stream-copies audio and embeds a JPEG cover (ffmpeg -c copy). It
does not encode audio or video, so a minimal LGPL build is sufficient.

How this project obtains ffmpeg
-------------------------------
The build script bundles ffmpeg as follows:
  - If bin\ffmpeg.exe already exists, it is used as-is.
  - Otherwise the build downloads the current LGPL "latest" Windows build from
    the BtbN FFmpeg-Builds project and extracts ffmpeg.exe into bin\.

The BtbN "latest" URL always serves the newest build, so anyone building this
project from scratch may receive a NEWER ffmpeg than the one recorded below.
The build warns on the console when the downloaded build's SHA-256 does not
match the tested value. This is expected and allowed under the LGPL; it only
affects which exact version you are then responsible for attributing.

